title: Saint Francis welcomes bye week after 8-0 start
text:
Saint Francis welcomes bye week after 8-0 start 
By Dean Pantazi - 21 Alive October 25, 2015 Updated Oct 25, 2015 at 9:14 PM EDT 
FORT WAYNE, Ind. (21 Alive) - After wins in each of their first eight games, NAIA seventh ranked Saint Francis will back things down this week with a bye on the schedule before the final two games of the regular season. 
Head coach Kevin Donley was pleased with the effort of his team in their 39-27 win at Robert Morris on Saturday, saying it showed the Cougars could be successful against a good team on the road. 
Donley and his staff will mix recruiting in this week with a scaled back practice schedule.
